==== CCL2 (MCP-1) and Symptom Severity

Montoya et al.\ (2017, $n = 192$) identified CCL2 (monocyte chemoattractant protein-1) among the cytokines most strongly correlating with ME/CFS symptom severity CCL2 drives monocyte and T-cell recruitment and reflects ongoing innate immune activation; its severity correlation makes it one of the stronger candidate immunological biomarkers from the cytokine literature.

